<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1094,1517]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Erect or ascending, densely and spreadingly branched, to 
<quantity box="[787,856,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="cm" value="18.0">18 cm</quantity>
tall. Shoots homophyllous, 
<quantity box="[1173,1295,1094,1121]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20 mm</quantity>
in diam. incl. leaves. Stems excl. leaves 
<quantity box="[445,562,1130,1157]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
thick at the base. Leaves borne in alternating, irregular whorls of 3–4, these 
<quantity box="[136,250,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
apart, patent-spreading to ascending, straight to slightly recurved, not twisted at the base, linear-lanceolate, widest at or above the middle, with a narrowed petiole-like lamina base, with short-acute to obtuse apex, 7–11 
<emphasis box="[1363,1382,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">×</emphasis>
1–1.2 (–1.5) mm, subcoriaceous, abaxially with prominent, decurrent vein, adaxially flat or slightly convex, with revolute, smooth margins. Leaf bases, especially in basal divisions with widening and prominently decurrent margins and vein. Sporangia ca. 
<quantity box="[295,360,1310,1337]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
